hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Who would I report to? webmail.metrodrug.id As Republican Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., has suggested, it would be catastrophic for the U.S. not to act and not to act now. If we don't act now, how will we degrade Assad's chemical weapon capabilities? How can we stop or slow down or prevent further mass murder of innocent men, women and children? How can the Free Syrian Army gain strength and how can we show our support for their opposition to Assad, his rule and his methods? As our Secretary of State John Kerry said, if we fail to act, we could lose our allies and as Sen. Menendez, D-N.J., stated, "we have an obligation to act."
